  "why": "The paper goes beyond merely reporting failures: it characterizes properties of the discovered failures (e.g., showing failures under specific input transformations such as lighting/occlusion), links failure-inducing tests to particular input features (Tables 3 and 4), correlates failures with model-internal signals (neuron activation / neuron coverage analyses), and uses generated failures to detect polluted training data (identifying 95.6% of mislabeled samples). However, it stops short of providing deeper causal root-cause analyses that systematically trace failures to underlying model vulnerabilities such as spurious feature reliance or overfitting across all cases. Thus the paper provides partial diagnostic insight (characterization and correlations) but not full explanatory diagnosis of underlying vulnerabilities for each failure.",
